message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Kazakhstan, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you have the time, walking can be a good option. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km on foot.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle, it can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. Cycling can take around 3-5 minutes to cover the 1km distance, depending on your speed.

3. Public Transportation: Check if there are any buses, trams, or minibusses (known as marshrutkas) that pass by or near the grocery store. Public transportation can be a cost-effective option, but the availability and frequency of services may vary depending on your location.

4. Taxi: If you prefer a more comfortable and direct option, you can take a taxi. Taxis are usually readily available in urban areas, and you can use ride-hailing apps or simply hail one on the street. Taxis are relatively affordable in Kazakhstan, and the ride should take only a few minutes.

Consider the weather conditions, your budget, and personal preferences when choosing the most suitable mode of transportation to reach the grocery store.
